column1: 23:20|It appeared afterwards that on the same evening
column3: he made another very eccentric and unexpected visit. The rain still persisted. Drenched to the skin
column4: he walked into the little flat where the parents of his betrothed lived
column5: in Third Street in Vassilyevsky Island.|Crime and Punishment|Fyodor Dostoyevsky

column2: he drove south to Laguna Beach. At eleven-twenty
column3: he parked his van across the street from the Hudston house.|Watchers|Dean Koontz

column2: which marked twenty past eleven. ""Then I'll sleep here till three and catch the four o'clock freight. They let us men from the Fleet ride free as a rule."""|Captains Courageous|Rudyard Kipling
